    term: 'AI Search',
    definition:
      'AI search refers to advanced search technologies that enable users to retrieve information using natural language processing and machine learning techniques, offering more intuitive, context-aware results compared to traditional keyword searches.',
    long_definition:
      '## AI Search\n\n### Overview\nAI search represents an evolution of traditional search methodologies by leveraging artificial intelligence to provide more accurate and context-sensitive search results. Unlike conventional keyword-based searches, which rely on exact terms, AI search systems use natural language processing (NLP) to understand the intent and context of the user\'s query. This allows users to interact with search systems using conversational language, much like they would when speaking to another person.\n\n### Key Components\n- **Natural Language Processing (NLP):** This is crucial for parsing and understanding user queries in their natural language form. It enables the search engine to interpret complex queries that include slang, synonyms, or multi-part questions.\n- **Machine Learning:** ML algorithms help in continuously improving search results by learning from interactions and feedback. They can predict user intent and rank results based on previous interactions and inferred preferences.\n\n### Examples and Use Cases\n- **E-commerce:** AI search engines can significantly enhance the shopping experience by understanding user queries like "show me summer dresses under $50." This fosters a more intuitive search that captures user intent and preferences.\n- **Enterprise Solutions:** In enterprise environments, AI search tools can help employees find documents and resources across vast knowledge bases using simple natural queries, thus boosting productivity and reducing search time.\n\n### Advantages\n- **Improved Accuracy:** AI search offers more relevant and precise results by understanding the semantic meaning of queries.\n- **User Experience:** The conversational nature of AI search queries aligns better with how users naturally seek information, thereby enhancing user satisfaction.\n\n### Insights\nAI search is continuously advancing, with applications expanding into areas like personal assistants and [chatbot integrations](https://docsbot.ai/documentation/developer/chat-api-overview) for business and personal use. As AI capabilities grow, so does the potential for AI search to transform our interaction with technology, making it more seamless and intuitive.',
