    term: 'Computer Vision',
    definition:
      'Computer vision is an interdisciplinary field that enables computers to interpret and process visual data from the world, such as images and videos.',
    long_definition:
      '## Overview\nComputer vision is a continually evolving field that involves methodologies for acquiring, processing, analyzing, and understanding visual data in the form of digital images and videos. Its ultimate objective is to automate tasks that the human visual system can accomplish.\n\n### Components\n- **Image Acquisition:** The first step in computer vision where images are captured through cameras or sensors.\n- **Image Processing:** This includes enhancements and filtering techniques to prepare images for further analysis.\n- **Feature Extraction:** Identifying and measuring distinctive characteristics or patterns in the image data.\n- **Recognition and Analysis:** This involves detecting objects within the images and understanding their context or generating descriptive captions.\n\n### Applications\n1. **Autonomous Vehicles:** Cars use computer vision to perceive and interpret their surroundings, helping with navigation and obstacle avoidance.\n2. **Healthcare:** Computer vision aids in medical image analysis, such as identifying tumors in MRI scans or retina scans.\n3. **Retail:** Helps in inventory management, cashier-less checkouts, and customer behavior analysis through surveillance footage.\n4. **Agriculture:** Enables automated monitoring of crops and livestock using drones or stationary cameras for health assessment and yield prediction.\n\n### Insights and Future Directions\n- Computer vision continues to expand with the integration of deep learning, enabling more sophisticated and accurate visual interpretations.\n- The field poses challenges, such as ensuring the robustness of models against poor lighting, occlusions, and varying viewing angles.\n- Ethical considerations, such as privacy concerns and bias in automated surveillance systems, are prominent discussions in the domain.\n- As an integral part of Artificial Intelligence solutions in many [industries](https://docsbot.ai/industry/business-information), from [Retail](https://docsbot.ai/industry/retail-sales) to [Healthcare](https://docsbot.ai/industry/pharmacy), computer vision is critical for future innovations in digital transformation.',
