    long_definition:
      "### Overview\nFLUX represents a groundbreaking suite in the realm of text-to-image generation, launched by Black Forest Labs. These models are at the frontier of generative AI, focusing on transforming textual descriptions into highly detailed and diverse images. At the core of FLUX's advancements are the developments in VQGAN, Latent Diffusion, and Adversarial Diffusion Distillation, all aimed at enhancing the efficiency and creative potential of generative media technologies.\n\n### Variations and Model Types\n- **FLUX.1 & FLUX1.1 [pro]:** This model is the pinnacle of FLUX's capabilities, offering state-of-the-art image generation with superior prompt adherence, visual quality, image detail, and diversity. It operates at impressive speeds, optimizing the synthesis process for those requiring top-tier performance.\n- **FLUX.1 [dev]:** An open-weight version available for non-commercial projects, it mirrors the performance of FLUX.1 [pro] while being more resource-efficient. It is designed to facilitate wider accessibility for developers and researchers.\n- **FLUX.1 [schnell]:** Tailored for speed and personal use, this model is available for local development. As an openly licensed model under Apache2.0, it ensures that developers have the flexibility to explore its capabilities in various personal projects.\n\n### Innovations and Use Cases\nFLUX is not just a series of models but a pioneering effort in pushing the boundaries of what generative AI can achieve concerning media synthesis. With its comprehensive suite, FLUX is poised to redefine applications in areas like digital art, media production, and creative industries where the transformation of written content to high-quality visual representation is essential. \n\n### Notable Insights\nThe release of FLUX models underscores a mission to democratize access to cutting-edge AI technologies, by enabling educators, researchers, and developers to harness these tools, potentially sparking new innovations across sectors. As part of its commitment, the availability of FLUX.1 [dev] on platforms like HuggingFace signals a deliberate effort to drive community engagement and foster advancements safely and effectively across the global AI landscape.\n\n### Conclusion\nBy offering diverse models catering to different needs\u2014from professional-grade outputs to local development-friendly versions\u2014FLUX establishes a new standard in text-to-image synthesis, enabling creators and developers to explore the vast potential of generative AI.",
