    term: 'Limited Memory',
    definition:
      'Limited Memory is a type of Artificial Intelligence (AI) system that learns from data derived from past experiences to make future decisions or predictions.',
    long_definition:
      '## Understanding Limited Memory AI\nLimited Memory AI refers to algorithms or systems that consider historical data to inform ongoing operations, enabling better predictions and decisions. This contrasts with reactive machines, which have no memory or data storage capabilities and are limited to current experiences.\n\n### How It Works\n- **Data Collection:** These systems gather information from experiences or observations through sensors or external inputs.\n- **Storing Data:** Crucially, limited memory systems must have storage capabilities to keep relevant past information.\n- **Model Updates:** With stored data, the information can be retrieved to improve accuracy in ongoing prediction models or decision-making processes.\n\n### Examples\n- **Autonomous Vehicles:** Self-driving cars observe the environment, combining previous and real-time data to navigate safely. They use models considering past driving events to predict future scenarios like road changes or object movements.\n- **Interactive Voice Assistants:** Limited memory helps voice assistants learn user preferences over time, improving response relevance through past interaction history.\n\n### Variations and User Cases\n- **Decision-Making Aids:** In predictive typing or text suggestions, limited memory helps improve word prediction by storing previous keystrokes or selections.\n- **Robotics and Automation:** Robots using limited memory can adapt routes in factories by recalling paths and obstacles previously encountered, optimizing path planning.\n\n### Advantages and Limitations\n- **Advantages:**\n  - **Improved Decision-Making and Prediction:** By recalling past data, these systems offer enhanced predictions and more informed decisions.\n  - **Learning Capability:** Systems equipped with limited memory can improve over time, adapting to changes and improving functionality.\n- **Limitations:**\n  - **Data Storage:** Requires storage infrastructure and strategies to manage and retrieve data efficiently.\n  - **Privacy and Security:** Handling of data can raise [privacy](https://docsbot.ai/legal/privacy-policy) and security concerns, especially in sensitive environments.',
