    term: 'ViT (Vision Transformer)',
    definition:
      'ViT (Vision Transformer) is an architecture that applies the transformer model, originally designed for natural language processing, to image analysis tasks.',
    long_definition:
      "## ViT (Vision Transformer)\n\n### Overview\nVision Transformers (ViT) are a groundbreaking approach in the field of computer vision, translating the mechanics of transformers from their original domain of natural language processing (NLP) to image processing. This innovation has enabled the ViT architecture to effectively handle various image-based tasks with increased precision and efficiency.\n\n### Architecture\nViT architectures consist of multiple transformer layers used to extract features from non-overlapping patches of an image. These patches are fed into the transformer model after embedding them into a suitable dimension, along with a positional encoding to retain spatial information.\n\n- **Patch Extraction:** Images are divided into fixed-size patches.\n- **Embedding:** Each patch is flattened and linearly embedded into a lower-dimensional space, typically matching the model's input size.\n- **Multi-Head Attention:** The core component, which enables parallel processing of multiple attention mechanisms, allowing the model to weigh different parts of the input differently.\n\n### Examples and Use Cases\n- **Image Classification:** ViT has shown state-of-the-art performance in image classification on benchmark datasets.\n- **Image Segmentation:** By leveraging ViT, tasks that involve identifying and labeling regions in an image, such as segmenting animals in wildlife photos, are efficiently executed.\n\nIn practice, ViTs can be seen in advanced AI systems that require high precision in image analysis tasks, ranging from autonomous vehicles to medical diagnostic tools.\n\n### Notable Insights\n- ViTs excel particularly when trained on very large datasets, often requiring the computational power comparable to traditional convolutional neural networks.\n- Due to their reliance on large-scale training data, many implementations of ViTs leverage pre-training on massive datasets followed by fine-tuning for specific tasks\u2014highlighting the importance of [custom training strategies](https://docsbot.ai/documentation/doc/training-a-chatbot-from-raw-data-csv).\n\nIn conclusion, the Vision Transformer marks a pivotal enhancement in image processing by merging the strengths of transformer models in handling data processing complexities, showcasing its versatility across a range of advanced applications.",
